><sec sec-type="other3"><title>Russian Federation</title><sec><title>East of the Urals</title><p>Ivan Meshkov et al. (737&#x02013;745) examine the variables affecting tuberculosis prevalence.</p></sec></sec><sec sec-type="other4"><title>United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland</title><sec><title>Measles vaccination coverage</title><p>Michael Edelstein et al. (754&#x02013;763) triangulate data sources.</p></sec></sec><sec sec-type="other5"><title>Global</title><sec><title>Paying for universal health coverage </title><p>Bernadette Ann-Marie O&#x02019;Hare (746&#x02013;753) estimates the potential health sector gains of addressing international corporate tax avoidance.</p></sec><sec><title>Physical fitness of young people</title><p>Neil Armstrong and Jo Welsman (777&#x02013;782) examine myths and misconceptions.</p></sec></sec></body></article>